strings.Value: "I know some of us would benefit from losing some weight, but I'm not about to starve with the rest!"
"Who is responsible for our rations? The poor dimwit should learn to count! We're running out of food again!"
"You pay too much attention to mundane things."
"Make a snare. Put it over there — look, where I'm pointing. And wait. Perhaps lunch will visit us soon."
"Perhaps if someone didn't gorge himself at every stop… On second thought, no — please, keep stuffing your face as always. Otherwise we might not be able to shut you up at all!"
"'We're running out of food!', 'I am so tired! I need to go to bed!', 'Oh, there's a plague going around, I'm so afraid! I might get sick!' — The living do nothing but whine."
"How so, master Jubilost?! Doesn't the great discoverer have a resourceful plan for such eventualities?"
"How so, master Jubilost?! Doesn't the great discoverer have a resourceful plan for such eventualities?"
